# GigKraft — Initial Basic Structure

## Final Decisions (Locked)

- **Repository layout:** Monorepo-style folders under:
  - `GigKraft/dev/backend`
  - `GigKraft/dev/frontend`
  - `GigKraft/dev/mobile`
- **Delivery model for MVP:** Phased approach
  - Phase 1: backend + UI with mocks/stubs
  - Phase 2: live integrations (Twilio/Stripe/S3/FCM/Google OAuth)
- **Service area UI (MVP):** ZIP list + radius slider only (no map UI)
- **Mobile strategy:** One mobile app with role-based flows
- **Auth model:** JWT + one `User` model with role (`pro`, `homeowner`, `node_manager`)
- **Node manager auth:** Google sign-in + email/password
- **Realtime strategy (MVP):** Polling first (WebSocket later in Phase 2+)
- **Credentials status:** Missing/incomplete locally; integration services mocked in development
- **WhatsApp:** Mock in local/dev until approval is available
- **Geography model:** Multi-node support
- **Homeowner billing/payments:** Not in MVP (no homeowner quote/invoice payment flow)
- **Design direction:** Keep color system; fonts can change; support 4 themes (including one dark)
- **Infrastructure target (MVP):** Local `docker-compose` only

